<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="130" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,644,1208]" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,304,751,776]" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">Remark.</emphasis>
This taxon was described by 
<bibRefCitation box="[650,812,751,776]" pageId="2" pageNumber="130" refId="ref4457" refString="Orhant, G. (2012) Deux nOuVeaux Agrisius Orientaux (LepidOptera, Arctiidae, LithOsiinae). Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de Mulhouse, 68 (3), 37 - 38." type="journal article">Orhant (2012)</bibRefCitation>
as a valid species without comparison with its closest relative 
<taxonomicName box="[242,372,788,812]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicu">
<emphasis box="[242,372,788,812]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">A. japonicu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s 
<bibRefCitation box="[390,532,788,813]" pageId="2" pageNumber="130" refId="ref4287" refString="Leech, J. H. (1889) 3. On the LepidOptera OF Japan and COrea. - Part II. HeterOcera, sect. I. Proceedings of the general meetings for scientific business of the Zoological Society of London, 1888, 580 - 654." type="journal article">Leech, 1889</bibRefCitation>
, and later 
<bibRefCitation box="[649,974,788,813]" pageId="2" pageNumber="130" refId="ref4160" refString="DubatOlOV, V. V. &amp; Kishida, Y. (2013) ReMarks On the species cOMpOsitiOn OF the genus Agrisius, With a descriptiOn OF a neW species FrOM LaOs (LepidOptera, Arctiidae: LithOsiinae). Tinea, 22 (3), 156 - 160." type="journal article">Dubatolov &amp; Kishida (2013)</bibRefCitation>
have suggested that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Orhant" authorityYear="2012" box="[1209,1329,788,812]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubatolovi">
<emphasis box="[1209,1329,788,812]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">dubatolovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might be a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leech" authorityYear="1889" box="[355,464,824,847]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[355,464,824,847]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The detailed comparison of its male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1072,1218,823,848]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[198,1420,201,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[164,1428,193,1903]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 21–26. Agrisius spp.: Male genitalia. 21, A. japonicus japonicus, S KOrea, slide YK2801 Kishida, re-MOunted by VOlynkin; 22, A. japonicus albida, paratype, China, Jiangsu, slide AV1882; 23, A. japonicus dubatolovi, hOlOtype, Thailand (aFter Orhant 2012); 24, A. japonicus dubatolovi, N VietnaM, slide AV1690 (ex prep. DubatOlOV); 25, A. orhanti, hOlOtype, S LaOs, slide AV3102; 26, A. leloii, paratype, C VietnaM, slide AV1777." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458424/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">Figs 23, 24</figureCitation>
) demonstrated its conspecificity with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leech" authorityYear="1889" box="[380,524,860,884]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[380,524,860,884]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">A. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[543,682,860,885]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[198,1420,201,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[164,1428,193,1903]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 21–26. Agrisius spp.: Male genitalia. 21, A. japonicus japonicus, S KOrea, slide YK2801 Kishida, re-MOunted by VOlynkin; 22, A. japonicus albida, paratype, China, Jiangsu, slide AV1882; 23, A. japonicus dubatolovi, hOlOtype, Thailand (aFter Orhant 2012); 24, A. japonicus dubatolovi, N VietnaM, slide AV1690 (ex prep. DubatOlOV); 25, A. orhanti, hOlOtype, S LaOs, slide AV3102; 26, A. leloii, paratype, C VietnaM, slide AV1777." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458424/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">Figs 21, 22</figureCitation>
). Nevertheless, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Orhant" authorityYear="2012" box="[868,988,860,884]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubatolovi">
<emphasis box="[868,988,860,884]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">dubatolovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has several morphological differences from 
<taxonomicName box="[212,341,896,919]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicu">
<emphasis box="[212,341,896,919]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">A. japonicu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s 
<taxonomicName box="[359,457,896,919]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicu">
<emphasis box="[359,457,896,919]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">japonicu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s therefore, here we treat it as a valid subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leech" authorityYear="1889" box="[1034,1174,896,919]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[1034,1174,896,919]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">A. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="130" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,644,1208]" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,932,957]" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Dubatolov &amp; Kishida" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Orhant" baseAuthorityYear="2012" box="[328,666,932,956]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="japonicus" subSpecies="dubatolovi">
<emphasis box="[328,666,932,956]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">Agrisius japonicus dubatolovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[680,781,932,957]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[235,1374,268,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[207,1379,267,1853]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Agrisius spp.: adults. 1, A. japonicus japonicus, ♂, Japan (©NHMUK); 2, A. japonicus japonicus, hOlOtype ♀, Japan (©NHMUK); 3, A. japonicus albida, paratype ♂, China, Jiangsu (ZFMK); 4, A. japonicus albida, paratype ♀, China, Jiangsu (ZFMK); 5, A. japonicus dubatolovi, holotype ♂, Thailand (after Orhant 2012); 6, A. japonicus dubatolovi, ♂, N VietnaM (SZMN); 7, A. orhanti, holotype ♂, S Laos (©NHMUK); 8, A. orhanti, paratype ♀, S Laos (CAV); 9, A. leloii, holotype ♂, C Vietnam (©NHMUK); 10, A. leloii, paratype ♀, C VietnaM (CAV)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458418/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">Figs 5, 6</figureCitation>
) is externally very similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[1114,1243,932,956]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicu">
<emphasis box="[1114,1243,932,956]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">A. japonicu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s 
<taxonomicName box="[1262,1360,933,956]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicu">
<emphasis box="[1262,1360,933,956]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">japonicu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[235,1374,268,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[207,1379,267,1853]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Agrisius spp.: adults. 1, A. japonicus japonicus, ♂, Japan (©NHMUK); 2, A. japonicus japonicus, hOlOtype ♀, Japan (©NHMUK); 3, A. japonicus albida, paratype ♂, China, Jiangsu (ZFMK); 4, A. japonicus albida, paratype ♀, China, Jiangsu (ZFMK); 5, A. japonicus dubatolovi, holotype ♂, Thailand (after Orhant 2012); 6, A. japonicus dubatolovi, ♂, N VietnaM (SZMN); 7, A. orhanti, holotype ♂, S Laos (©NHMUK); 8, A. orhanti, paratype ♀, S Laos (CAV); 9, A. leloii, holotype ♂, C Vietnam (©NHMUK); 10, A. leloii, paratype ♀, C VietnaM (CAV)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458418/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">Figs 1, 2</figureCitation>
) by grey wing coloration, but differs by the slightly larger size and the somewhat narrower forewing. Both those subspecies are geographically separated by 
<taxonomicName authority="Daniel, 1952" authorityName="Daniel" authorityYear="1952" box="[705,983,1004,1029]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="japonicus" subSpecies="albida">
<emphasis box="[705,829,1004,1028]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">A. j. albida</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[835,983,1004,1029]" pageId="2" pageNumber="130" refId="ref4041" refString="Daniel, F. (1952) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Arctiidae Ostasiens unter besOnderer Berucksichtigung der Ausbeuten VOn Dr. h. c. H. Hone aus dieseM Gebiet (Lep. - Het.). Bonner zoologische Beitrage, 3 (1 - 2 &amp; 3 - 4), 75 - 90 &amp; 305 - 324." type="journal article">Daniel, 1952</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which has whitish wing coloration. The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Volynkin &amp; Dubatolov &amp; Kishida" authorityYear="2018" baseAuthorityName="Orhant" baseAuthorityYear="2012" box="[349,618,1040,1064]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="japonicus" subSpecies="dubatolovi">
<emphasis box="[349,618,1040,1064]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">A. japonicus dubatolovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[634,763,1039,1064]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[198,1420,201,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[164,1428,193,1903]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 21–26. Agrisius spp.: Male genitalia. 21, A. japonicus japonicus, S KOrea, slide YK2801 Kishida, re-MOunted by VOlynkin; 22, A. japonicus albida, paratype, China, Jiangsu, slide AV1882; 23, A. japonicus dubatolovi, hOlOtype, Thailand (aFter Orhant 2012); 24, A. japonicus dubatolovi, N VietnaM, slide AV1690 (ex prep. DubatOlOV); 25, A. orhanti, hOlOtype, S LaOs, slide AV3102; 26, A. leloii, paratype, C VietnaM, slide AV1777." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458424/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">Figs 23, 24</figureCitation>
) differ from those of two other subspecies (
<figureCitation box="[1262,1392,1039,1064]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[198,1420,201,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[164,1428,193,1903]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 21–26. Agrisius spp.: Male genitalia. 21, A. japonicus japonicus, S KOrea, slide YK2801 Kishida, re-MOunted by VOlynkin; 22, A. japonicus albida, paratype, China, Jiangsu, slide AV1882; 23, A. japonicus dubatolovi, hOlOtype, Thailand (aFter Orhant 2012); 24, A. japonicus dubatolovi, N VietnaM, slide AV1690 (ex prep. DubatOlOV); 25, A. orhanti, hOlOtype, S LaOs, slide AV3102; 26, A. leloii, paratype, C VietnaM, slide AV1777." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458424/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">Figs 21, 22</figureCitation>
) by the uncus shape, which has the longer dorsal processes of its distal branches (thus, the distance between the apex of the dorsal process and the lobe-like rounded crest is the shortest, compared with other subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leech" authorityYear="1889" box="[1279,1420,1112,1135]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Agrisius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[1279,1420,1112,1135]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="130">A. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and also by the smaller vinculum and the somewhat longer distal saccular process.
</paragraph>
